Description: Penguicon Open Source and Science Fiction Convention in Southeast Michigan
Headquarters Regions: Greater Detroit Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Penguicon is a three-day event where we all learn from each other (as well as from our Guests of Honor) about hacking, building sci-fi universes, soldering, painting miniatures, gaming, coding, music, incredible costumes, and more. Our two pillars are Science Fiction and Open Source, but we cover as many diverse nerdy interests as possible. We have a consuite with free soda, coffee, munchies and other real food, which makes it easier on your budget. You can find all kinds of original artwork and non-commodity crafts in our enormous Maker Market. Over 1,300 nerds, geeks, and fans attend Penguicon every year to celebrate and share in what we all love. We are an all-volunteer, not-for-profit convention which brings together every kind of geek – software developers, moviemakers, authors and their fans, hackers, foodies – for a weekend of sharing in panels, workshops, and parties. Dozens of people work on the convention throughout the year, for no more than a pat on the back as people come ‘home’ to Penguicon each year. Penguicon has helped people collaborate on new art projects, meet life-long friends and change careers.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Media and Entertainment, Music and Audio, Other, Software

Description: Quant the News provides stock analysis, alerts, and impact assessment services.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Quant the News uses  Artificial Intelligence to convert news into numbers, in an attempt to quantify the impact of news. The company is launching its first product at TechCrunch called StockMood.  Which can be found at www.StockMood.com StockMood.com uses analyze news stories, classify their sentiment, and then measure their potential impact on a stock's price direction. Each article is individually ingested, and its sentiment assessed by natural language processing models. While the models aren't perfect, users can correct the sentiment rating produced by the system.  This crowd-sourcing technology allows the AI engine to constantly improve its accuracy. Mood measures how a stockâ€™s price responds to news. When a stock is in a good Mood that means the stock price responds very favorably to good news, and has a tendency to shrug off the bad news. The opposite is true for bad Mood. The more this happens the stronger the mood in that direction gets. When both the mood and the sentiment values for a stock reach certain empirically determined thresholds, a Sentiment Alert is issued, indicating a statistical probability for movement over the next 5 days. Sentiment alerts can be positive or negative. These Alerts  suggest that a stock may be at a peak of optimism or a peak of pessimism, respectively.  Our statistical analyses have shown that, at the time of an Overoptimism or Overpessimism Alert,  trading in the opposite direction of the news can provide significant edge.
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Content and Publishing, Data and Analytics, Financial Services, Media and Entertainment, Science and Engineering, Software

Description: The aim of Healthy Soda, Inc. and its signature product, Chill Low Glycemic Organic Soda, is to provide today's consumers the most .
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The aim of Healthy Soda, Inc. and its signature product, Chill Low Glycemic Organic Soda, is to provide today's consumers the most innovative, delicious, healthy alternative to traditional soda. Soda has been vilified, many believe rightfully so, as one of the greatest threats to public health. Why is soda so much worse than other culprits? Because it’s so popular, people love it, and they have been conditioned to drink it regularly for over a century now. The problem is, all current varieties of traditional soda, be them regular or diet, are fraught with health concerns. The idea for a healthy soda came about when our founder’s sister, a teacher, saw traditional sodas being taken out of schools. They were exchanged with other beverages that were still full of sugar and had just as many, if not more, calories than the soda they replaced. Someone needed to come up with a better alternative. We knew the big soda guys would never bring to market something that competed directly with their core business, so it was up to us to make a truly healthy soda. Making a great tasting healthy soda wasn't easy. We had to completely invent a new proprietary sweetening system, incorporate functional benefits that speak to the needs of today, and do everything to the highest standards to meet the requirements for USDA Organic and Kosher certification. We are very proud of our product, answering a need that is woefully unmet in the marketplace. So we think we have a great product, but how can we know for sure? We thought, let’s get some public reaction by going on that show Shark Tank and see what everyone else thinks. Well, we did that and in addition to getting a $50k seed investment from Shark Barbara Corcoran, we were also able to gain valuable feedback from real world consumers/retailers with an overwhelming positive reaction and demand for product. Help us make the healthy soda revolution a reality for everyone and the more money we raise, the bigger difference we can make!

Full Description: OpenedOrNot  by 500apps is an email tracking extension for Chrome web browser that allows users to track the status of their sent emails. The extension adds an icon to the Gmail interface that indicates when an email has been sent, received, and read. It also provides a notification when the email is opened. Features: Email tracking- Get notified as soon as your email is read by the recipient. The subject of the email, the recipient's information, and the time are all included in your notification. Read Receipt- Receive read receipts when recipients open an email on their desktop. When an email is sent, you'll see a single green checkmark, and when it is opened, you'll see a double green checkmark. Link-click Tracking- Link-click displays which emails were opened and which links were clicked. It shows how many times each link was clicked. Daily Reports- Access detailed reports on your tracked emails. Tracked emails, read emails, overall read count, and unread emails can all be viewed.

Description: Enjoy a rejuvenating Colorado vacation when you stay in Creekside Chalets & Cabins. Tucked away in the mountains and minutes from skiing.
Full Description: Located in the picturesque Arkansas River Valley, Creekside Chalets & Cabins are a wonderful choice for your next Colorado vacation. Whether you're visiting in the winter or the summer, you'll be perfectly situated to enjoy all that the area has to offer. Just minutes away, you'll find Monarch Mountain, which offers 800 skiable acres and receives an average of over 350 inches of snow every year. There are a number of other great winter activities nearby, including snowshoeing, dog sled rides, snowmobile tours, and cross-country skiing. Planning on visiting in the summer? You won't be disappointed either. The valley is home to a number of hiking and biking trails. With the Arkansas River nearby, there are also plenty of chances for fishing and whitewater rafting. You can also choose to explore the backcountry by way of an ATV tour or a horseback ride. Creekside Chalets & Cabins are just a short drive from Salida, Colorado, which is known as the Gem of the Rockies. This adorable town hosts a variety of festivas and events throughout the year and it's home to wonderful variety of shops and restaurants. If you want to explore the area a little more, there are several great attractions nearby. Both the Great Sand Dunes National Park and the Royal Gorge Bridge and Park are about a 1.5-hour (or less) drive away. The Great Sand Dunes is a great spot for wildlife viewing, hiking, sand sledding, and horseback riding. At the Royal Gorge, you'll enjoy some amazing views as well as a number of attractions like a gondola and zip line. Start planning your next Colorado vacation and book your stay at Creekside Chalets & Cabins today!

Reducing Food Waste While Feeding the Hungry and make a profit at the same time
Full Description: A new program—E-Dinner-- has been developed to feed America’s hungry by having verified needy people collect the nations surplus food DIRECTLY FROM FOOD PURVEYORS for their consumption. There is no need for the transport, refrigeration, recooking or re-serving of this excess food, all of which takes manpower and money. After being vetted and pre qualified, they will simply be notified by participating food purveyors (restaurants, arenas, grocery stores, etc.) of the availability of excess food at the food purveyors’ locations nearby. They (and the food purveyor) will be given a code and pick the food up within a stated period of time.  The result is a two way “Win” for all involved. First and foremost, the hungry get fed quality excess food. Second, the food purveyors will see a significant reduction in the enormous cost of the disposal of food waste, as well as gaining a tax write-off for the donation of this excess food to a qualified 501 (c)(3) charity.

Description: CapGain Solutions helps investors liquid worthless stocks to realize capital losses on income taxes.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: CapGain Solutions helps venture capitalists, private equity general partners and angel investors divest private assets to realize taxable losses that offset other taxable gains.  CapGain Solutions purchases private assets such as common stock, preferred stock, private notes and the like enabling investors to divest stranded "zombie" assets and realize tax losses that shield capital gains (and in some cases ordinary income for Section 1244 stock). The company offers turn-key services that provide the definitive, defensible documentation, process and procedures necessary to realize and recognize your capital losses in the current year. Selling to CapGain Solutions can be especially helpful if the company the investor wants to write off has not been closed with formal legal documentation or is still operating but "walking dead," and the tax write off is worth more to the investor than owning the stock.
